On May 25th and 26th, Hello Muffin Shop is participating in an AWESOME event- the Enough is Enough Collab! Swipe to see everything happening this weekend and read below for more details! 👇🏻 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
$1 from each sticker sheet sold in my shop during this two day event will be donated to Planned Parenthood. Drop “Enough is Enough” in the notes to seller at checkout to indicate your participation! ⭐️(Note: Please do not combine with coupon codes if participating in this event!)⭐️ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
There is a digital item bundle that comes with proof of a $10 donation to Planned Parenthood- local or national branches. Many other shops are also donating portions of weekend sales on physical items. To check out the other 💫 AMAZING 💫shops participating in this event and find out how you can get your hands on the digital item bundle, click the link in our bio! ✨
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Don’t forget: 100% of all profits of any items sold in the Enough is Enough Teespring shop go to Planned Parenthood! ✨ The link for this shop is also located in the bio! ✨

I absolutely support this! Although the ones about "no uterus no vote" kinds hurts as I had to have a full hysterectomy at 22, but I'm avid on supporting reproductive rights. ❤

@colleensplanner Hi! Thanks so much for your support! I completely understand what you mean. I’m not certain which shop has that in their contribution, but if you wanted to support the cause without getting that particular artwork, the TeeSpring shop has other designs as well as some shops donating a portion of sales with no specific designs (like my shop is doing $1 of each sheet in the entire shop sold.) 💜💜💜
@hellomuffinshop I'm not mad about it or anything. I know this is in such amazing faith and support of the issues right now, I will still be purchasing!! But thanks for your response ❤❤
Thank you ☺️ and thank you for participating
